          The Artist House at 534 Eaton Street‚ÄîRobert the Doll's original home‚Äîis now a bed-and-breakfast where guests in the turret room have reported hearing footsteps, children's laughter, and objects moving on their own. The East Martello Fort, built in 1862 and never completed, houses not only Robert but also the remains of Elena Milagro de Hoyos, a young woman whose body was taken from a mausoleum by Carl von Cosel, a radiology technician obsessed with her, who kept her preserved corpse in his home for seven years.
        </p>
